  "summary": {
    "as": "Reported to House",
    "asOf": "2022-12-14",
    "date": "2023-08-08T18:51:07Z",
    "text": "Ending Taxpayer Welfare for Oil and Gas Companies Act of 2021\n\nThis bill addresses royalties related to the development of federal energy resources.\n\nAmong other requirements, the bill\n\n increases the onshore royalty rates for new oil, gas, and coal leases; increases onshore rental rates for oil and gas leasing; modifies the current onshore oil and gas minimum bid from $2 to $10 and requires it to be adjusted every four years for inflation; and increases inspection fees and penalties on oil and gas operators."
  },
